A hundred and ninety eight of the new patients were found in Nairobi County, which remained in the lead in terms of the number of infections recorded daily per county. The number of declared Covid-19 infections in Kenya on Tuesday rose by 345 to 106,470, Health minister Mutahi Kagwe announced in a statement, saying 5,550 samples had been tested within a day. 

The Cabinet Secretary said the country had tested at least 1,306,601 samples for the disease by March 2, since reporting its first case on March 13, 2020. 



